# Styling Conventions

Follow these patterns when writing or editing styles.

## Units & Spacing

- Use `rem` for font sizes, padding, margin, and gap
- Use `px` only for borders and fine-grained values (e.g. `1px`, `2px`)
- Prefer `gap` over margin for flex/grid layouts

## Typography

- Use system font stacks: `system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif` or similar
- Avoid generic web fonts (Inter, Roboto, Arial) as defaults
- Use `font-weight` for hierarchy (e.g. 600–700 for headings)

## Colors & Theme

- Align with the no-purple-blue rule: avoid purple/blue as primary accents
- Use semantic neutrals for dark themes: `#1a1a1a` (bg), `#252525` (surface), `#444` (border), `#e0e0e0` (text), `#888` (muted)
- Define accent colors with warm or cool alternatives (teal, amber, coral, emerald)

## Interactions

- Add `transition` for hover/focus state changes (e.g. `transition: border-color 0.2s, background 0.2s`)
- Include `:focus` styles with visible outline or border change
- Use `cursor: pointer` on interactive elements

## Layout

- Use `box-sizing: border-box` globally
- Prefer `max-width` + `margin: 0 auto` for centered content
- Use flexbox with `flex-direction: column` and `gap` for form/control layouts
